'''''Star Wars Insider'' 62''' is the sixty-second issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands in [[October]] [[2002]]. This marked the first ''Star Wars Insider'' issue published by [[Paizo Publishing]] as well as the start of the magazine being released eight times a year, an increase from ''Star Wars Insider''{{'s}} former bimonthly publication schedule, which began with [[Star Wars Insider|issue 35]] in [[September]] [[1997]]. Issue 62 came packaged with an exclusive [[Topps]] trading card from the set [[2002 Topps Star Wars: Attack of the Clones Widevision|2002 Topps ''Star Wars: Attack of the Clones'' Widevision]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*From the Editor's Desk
*[[Rebel Rumblings]]
*[[Star News]]: From the World of Lucasfilm {{C|by [[Benjamin Harper]]}}
*[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader Catalog]]
*[[Behind the Magic]] &mdash; Digital Doubles {{C|by [[Rob Coleman]]}}
*[[Gamescape]] &mdash; Battle of the Planets, ''Star Wars'' Galaxies, and ''[[Arms & Equipment Guide]]'' {{C|by [[Brett Rector]], [[W. Haden Blackman|Haden Blackman]], and [[Brian Campbell]]}}
*[[Bookshelf]] &mdash; Manifest Destiny {{C|by Jason Fry}}
*[[Comics Link]] &mdash; Points of View {{C|by Daniel Wallace}}
*[[Set Piece]] &mdash; The ''Millennium Falcon'' {{C|by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]] & [[Chris Reiff]]}}
*[[Scouting the Galaxy]] &mdash; Sordid Tales from the Collecting World {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*[[Crossword (department)|Crossword]] &mdash; A Crash Course in Shyriiwook {{C|by [[Michael Selinker]]}}
*[[Star Wars Q&A|''Star Wars'' Q&A]] {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*[[The Last Page]] {{C|by [[Tony Moseley]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Prequel Update]]" {{C|by [[Dave Gross]]}}
*:<small>Producer [[Rick McCallum]] talks about the [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']] [[Star Wars home video releases|DVD]], [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|Episode III]], and [[George Lucas]]'s plans beyond ''[[Star Wars]]''.</small>
*"[[Inside Attack of the Clones|Inside ''Attack of the Clones'']]" {{C|by [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]]}}
*:<small>Just when you thought summer was over, ''Insider'' takes you back to camp—the camp of the notorious [[Tusken Raider/Legends|Tusken Raiders]]!</small>
*"[[Who's Who in the Jedi Order]]" {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*:<small>A brief history of sixteen of the most famous guardians of peace and justice in the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], including this issue's cover [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]], [[Aayla Secura/Legends|Aayla Secura]].</small>
*"[[Fightsaber: Jedi Lightsaber Combat]]" {{C|by David West Reynolds}}
*:<small>Through the millennia, Jedi have rigorously trained in the seven forms of [[Lightsaber combat/Legends|lightsaber combat]]. Examples from all five ''Star Wars'' movies illustrate these complex and ancient fighting styles.</small>
*"[[Starships of Episode II]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>It's no coincidence that the [[Delta-7 Aethersprite-class light interceptor/Legends|Jedi Starfighter]] looks like a miniature [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Imperial Star Destroyer]]. After all, [[Kuat Drive Yards/Legends|Kuat Drive Yards]] built them both.</small>
*"[[Return to Endor: The Stars of the Ewok Films Remember Their Adventure| The Stars of the Ewok Films Remember Their Adventure]]" {{C|by [[Rich Handley]]}}
*:<small>''Insider'' catches up with the casts of [[Caravan of Courage: An Ewok Adventure|''The Ewok Adventure'']] and ''[[Ewoks: The Battle for Endor]]''.</small>
*"[[Cardboard Cinema: Topps to Release First Attack of the Clones Widevision Set|Cardboard Cinema: Topps to Release First ''Attack of the Clones'' Widevision Set]]" {{C|by [[Michael Mikaelian]]}}
*:<small>Topps' latest ''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'' Widevision movie card set focuses on the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|Battle of Geonosis]], and it includes the first-ever widevision autograph cards.</small>
*"[[Emissary of the Void]]": Episode IV Relic of Ruin" {{C|by [[Greg Keyes]]}}
*:<small>''Insider''{{'s}} premier installment of Greg Keyes' [[Star Wars: The New Jedi Order|The New Jedi Order]] serial drops you right in the middle of the action. Catch up on the first three installments for free at [[StarWars.com|'''starwars.com''']]</small>

